@startuml fig-A09-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title SDN IPS — E2 Flow (Detect → Block → Expire → Recover)

participant "h1\n(attacker)" as ATK #FFCDD2
participant "s1\n(OVS)" as SW #BBDEFB
participant "h2\n(victim)" as VIC #C8E6C9
participant "IDS\n(h3)" as IDS #E3F2FD
participant "Controller" as C #E1BEE7

== PHASE 1 — ATTACK (before blocking) ==

ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 22
SW -> VIC : forwarded
ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 80
SW -> VIC : forwarded
ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 443 ... (>=10 ports)
note right of SW : R3: SYN (ack==0) >= 10

IDS -> IDS : aggregate: >=N SYNs\nin time window
IDS -[#E53935]> C : POST /block\n{"src": "h1_ip", "duration": 30}
note right of C : R1: tcp.port==6653 >= 1

== PHASE 2 — BLOCKING ==

C -> C : validate + whitelist check
C -> SW : flow-mod: match src=h1_ip\naction=drop, priority=500\nidle_timeout=30
note right of C : R2: tcp.port==6653\n&& tcp.len>0 >= 5

ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN → port 25
SW -[#E53935]>x SW : dropped by block rule
ATK -[#E53935]> SW : SYN retransmission
SW -[#E53935]>x SW : dropped
note right of SW #FFCDD2 : no traffic reaches victim

== PHASE 3 — LEGITIMATE TRAFFIC (contrast) ==

VIC -[#43A047]> SW : ICMP ping → h1
SW -[#43A047]> ATK : forwarded (return allowed)
note right of SW : R4: icmp || tcp >= 1

== PHASE 4 — EXPIRY AND RECOVERY ==

... idle_timeout expires (30 s) ...
SW -> SW : block rule removed
ATK -> SW : SYN → port 80
SW -> VIC : forwarded again
note right of SW #E8F5E9 : traffic resumes after expiry

legend right
  Before blocking: scan traffic reaches victim.
  After blocking: drop rule prevents delivery.
  After expiry: traffic flows again.
  All transitions visible in PCAP and dump-flows.
endlegend
@enduml
